Equipment/tools used to create and run CAMMY the colour-mixing cyber-physical system (CPS).

Computer setup equipment:
- Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ - https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-3-model-b-plus/
- Monitor with HDMI cable
- Keyboard with USB connection
- Mouse with USB connection
- SanDisk Ultra microSDHC UHS-I card with adapter - https://www.officeworks.com.au/shop/officeworks/p/sandisk-ultra-32gb-sdhc-uhs-i-memory-card-sdsdun432
- Raspberry Pi Universal Power Supply (2.5A, 5.1V) - https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-universal-power-supply/

Camera setup equipment:
- Raspberry Pi Camera V2 - https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/camera-module-v2/

LED matrix setup equipment:
- GST60A05-PJ1 Adaptor (6A, 5V)
- Universal power cord (i.e. with C13 female connector)
- RGB Matrix Bonnet for Raspberry Pi - https://www.adafruit.com/product/3211
- RGB LED matrix (64x32 - 6mm pitch) - https://www.adafruit.com/product/2276
- GPIO ribbon cable
- LED matrix power cable

Paint setup equipment:
- Terumo 5mL luer lock syringes (at least 5 syringes) - https://www.mcfarlanemedical.com.au/19065TE/SYRINGE-5ML-LUER-LOCK-TERUMO-%28ISS%2A05L%29--BOX_or_100/pd.php
- Acrylic paint (cyan, magenta, yellow, white, black - or combinations that can achieve these colours)

